<br>
-Kai <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grogofrogslaughter>Grogo Frogslaughter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Must...Kill...Froggies...</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/26/02 10:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=488.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ameritech.net/users/gwheeler/froggie.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 4th shawl, cursed or bugged?</span><hr size=1> I'd also like to throw my support behind the &quot;Follow the Pet&quot; route.  Those triggers are damn near impossible to just happen upon.  Mage earth pets work the best, as do shammy pets, as you can see exactly where they are looking, and follow them to the trigger.  <br>
